New Records: Giannis Antetokounmpo recorded a triple-double with 11 points, 12 rebounds, and 13 assists.
The Milwaukee Bucks snapped a two-game skid with this victory.
Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo's standout performance with a season-high 13 assists set the tone.
Khris Middleton's absence due to injury was noted.
The Bucks handled the 8-28 Raptors convincingly despite the injury.
Pre-Game Insights: The Bucks had lost four of their last five matches before this win.
The Raptors had a poor 8-28 record entering the game.
Post-Match Reflections: Bucks coach Doc Rivers praised Antetokounmpo's performance and its impact on the team.
The victory ended the Bucks' two-game skid.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Giannis Antetokounmpo suffered a cut on his right little finger during the game.
